  "text": "The xDS configuration update flow follows a bidirectional gRPC stream architecture:\n\n**1. Protocol Definition Layer (envoyproxy/data-plane-api):**\nThe AggregatedDiscoveryService in envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads.proto defines two RPC methods:\n- StreamAggregatedResources(stream DiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DiscoveryResponse) - for state-of-the-world xDS\n- DeltaAggregatedResources(stream DeltaDiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DeltaDiscoveryResponse) - for delta xDS\n\nThe message types are defined in envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto:\n- DiscoveryRequest and DiscoveryResponse for state-of-the-world mode\n- DeltaDiscoveryRequest and DeltaDiscoveryResponse for delta mode\nBoth message types include version_info, type_url, resource_names, and node information for proper xDS versioning and resource tracking.\n\n**2. Control Plane Implementation (envoyproxy/go-control-plane):**\nThe go-control-plane repository provides:\n- Generated Go types in envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.pb.go and ads_grpc.pb.go from the protobuf definitions\n- A control plane server implementation in pkg/server/v3/server.go that implements the AggregatedDiscoveryServiceServer interface\n- The server handles StreamAggregatedResources and DeltaAggregatedResources gRPC calls from Envoy clients\n\n**3. Data Plane Client Implementation (envoyproxy/envoy):**\nEnvoy's xDS client-side implementation in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/ manages subscriptions:\n\n- GrpcSubscriptionImpl (grpc_subscription_impl.h/.cc): Adapter class that converts typed Subscription calls into untyped GrpcMux calls. The start() method initiates subscription to resources via addWatch().\n\n- GrpcMuxImpl (grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc): Manages state-of-the-world xDS, implements GrpcMux interface, handles DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse streaming. Uses GrpcStreamCallbacks<DiscoveryResponse> callbacks.\n\n- NewGrpcMuxImpl (new_grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc): Manages delta xDS, implements the newer delta protocol using DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse messages through GrpcStreamCallbacks<DeltaDiscoveryResponse>.\n\n- GrpcStream (grpc_stream.h): Template class that wraps the underlying gRPC AsyncClient, establishes bidirectional streams, handles message sending (sendMessage), and routes incoming responses to callbacks via onReceiveMessage().\n\n- DeltaSubscriptionState (delta_subscription_state.h/.cc): Maintains per-resource versions and subscription state for delta xDS.\n\n**Configuration Update Flow:**\n1. Envoy calls GrpcSubscriptionImpl::start() with resource names to subscribe to\n2. This calls GrpcMuxImpl::addWatch() (for SotW) or similar for delta, which establishes a gRPC stream\n3. GrpcStream::establishNewStream() creates the bidirectional channel using Grpc::RawAsyncClient\n4. Envoy sends DiscoveryRequest messages with resource_names, type_url, and version_info\n5. Control plane receives the request, processes it, and sends back DiscoveryResponse with updated resources\n6. GrpcStream::onReceiveMessage() processes the response and invokes GrpcStreamCallbacks\n7. The response is decoded and passed to SubscriptionCallbacks::onConfigUpdate() for application to the data plane\n8. Envoy ACKs the update by sending a DiscoveryRequest with the new nonce/version_info"
}

